  "text": "RC-3095, a selective GRPR antagonist, has been shown to have anti-inflammatory properties in murine models of arthritis, gastritis, uveitis, and sepsis by attenuating the release of proinflammatory cytokines such as tumor necrosis factor-alpha (TNF-) and interleukin-1-beta (IL-1 ) and the activation and migration of mononuclear cells to sites of inflammation [CITATION_1] . In addition, GRP mediates air pollutioninduced airway hyperreactivity and inflammation in rodents [CITATION_2] .",
